Note:
==============================================================================
UCD_GENERATOR - Pure-Runa Unicode Character Database Table Generator
==============================================================================

This tool parses the authoritative Unicode Character Database files and
emits the canonical-decomposition / property tables consumed by
codepoint.runa and normalized_string.runa via the accessors exposed in
codepoint_unicode_tables.runa.

The output file is structurally identical to the curated baseline that
ships in codepoint_unicode_tables.runa - same accessor surface, same
module-global layout, same init proc shape - but contains the FULL
Unicode 15.1.0 dataset instead of the curated European-text subset.

DESIGN PHILOSOPHY:

This program is a SOURCE-TO-SOURCE generator. It does not need to run
on the same machine as the compiler that builds the compiler. It runs
once per UCD release, emits a Runa source file, and that file is then
checked into the repository alongside this generator. This is the same
pattern Go uses for golang.org/x/text/unicode and Rust uses for
unicode-rs/unicode-normalization.

DEPENDENCIES:

The generator requires the following UCD files in a local directory
(default /tmp/ucd/, configurable via the UCD_DIR constant below):

  UnicodeData.txt              - Core property + decomposition data
  DerivedNormalizationProps.txt - NFC_QC / NFD_QC / NFKC_QC / NFKD_QC
  CompositionExclusions.txt    - Codepoints to skip during NFC compose
  CaseFolding.txt              - Full case-folding mappings
  DerivedCoreProperties.txt    - Alphabetic / Lowercase / Uppercase /
                                  ID_Start / ID_Continue / ...

Fetch the official Unicode 15.1.0 release:
    curl -O https://www.unicode.org/Public/15.1.0/ucd/UCD.zip
    unzip UCD.zip -d /tmp/ucd/

Then run the generator. The output replaces codepoint_unicode_tables.runa
in the working tree:

    /tmp/runac_92 tools/ucd_generator.runa /tmp/gen.s
    <link with primitives + runtime>
    ./generator > compiler/frontend/primitives/text/codepoint_unicode_tables.runa

OUTPUT SHAPE:

The emitter writes a Runa source file with the exact same module-level
structure as the curated baseline:
  - Same Constant declarations for GC_*, HANGUL_*
  - Same module-global Let declarations
  - Same accessor proc bodies (binary search)
  - Replaced install_* procs with full-population variants whose body
    is a long sequence of unicode_write_* calls
  - Same top-level codepoint_unicode_tables_init driver

This is a deliberate design choice: the curated baseline IS the
generator's output shape, just with curated data. Swapping in the full
dataset is a drop-in replacement.

PARSING:

UnicodeData.txt format (UAX #44 section 5.7.4):
  Each line is semicolon-delimited with 15 fields:
    0: Code value (hex)
    1: Name
    2: General_Category
    3: Canonical_Combining_Class (decimal)
    4: Bidi_Class
    5: Decomposition_Type and_Mapping
    6-8: Numeric values
    9-10: Bidi mirrored / Unicode 1 name
    11: ISO comment (obsolete)
    12: Simple uppercase (hex)
    13: Simple lowercase (hex)
    14: Simple titlecase (hex)
  Trailing blank line ends the record. Range entries use
  "<First>" / "<Last>" suffixes in the name field.

DerivedNormalizationProps.txt: Each non-comment line is
  "<codepoint or range> ; <property> [; <value>]" e.g.
  "00A0 ; NFKD_QC; N"

CompositionExclusions.txt: Each non-comment line is a single
  hexadecimal codepoint, optionally followed by a comment.

CaseFolding.txt: Each non-comment line is
  "<codepoint> ; <status>; <mapping>; # <comment>" where status is
  one of C (Common), F (Full), S (Simple), T (Turkic).

DerivedCoreProperties.txt: Each non-comment line is
  "<codepoint or range> ; <property>" e.g.
  "0041..005A    ; Uppercase"

OUTPUT FILE STRUCTURE:

The emitter walks the in-memory tables in sorted order and writes a
sequence of writer calls. For long tables we emit them in chunks of
1000 entries per helper proc to stay within stage1's parser limits.

REFERENCES:
- UAX #44 Unicode Character Database (formal data formats)
- The UnicodeData.txt header documents every field's syntax
- https://www.unicode.org/Public/15.1.0/ucd/
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StrCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/assembly/syscall.runa" as Syscall

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Constant UCD_O_RDONLY as Integer is 0
Constant UCD_O_WRONLY as Integer is 1
Constant UCD_O_CREAT as Integer is 64
Constant UCD_O_TRUNC as Integer is 512
Constant UCD_WRITE_FLAGS as Integer is 577
Constant UCD_FILE_MODE as Integer is 420

Constant UCD_BUFFER_SIZE as Integer is 1048576

Note: GC string -> id mapping is materialized via the gc_id_from_str proc
Note: below. Values match the GC_* constants in
Note: codepoint_unicode_tables.runa.

Constant UCD_GC_LU as Integer is 1
Constant UCD_GC_LL as Integer is 2
Constant UCD_GC_LT as Integer is 3
Constant UCD_GC_LM as Integer is 4
Constant UCD_GC_LO as Integer is 5
Constant UCD_GC_MN as Integer is 6
Constant UCD_GC_MC as Integer is 7
Constant UCD_GC_ME as Integer is 8
Constant UCD_GC_ND as Integer is 9
Constant UCD_GC_NL as Integer is 10
Constant UCD_GC_NO as Integer is 11
Constant UCD_GC_PC as Integer is 12
Constant UCD_GC_PD as Integer is 13
Constant UCD_GC_PS as Integer is 14
Constant UCD_GC_PE as Integer is 15
Constant UCD_GC_PI as Integer is 16
Constant UCD_GC_PF as Integer is 17
Constant UCD_GC_PO as Integer is 18
Constant UCD_GC_SM as Integer is 19
Constant UCD_GC_SC as Integer is 20
Constant UCD_GC_SK as Integer is 21
Constant UCD_GC_SO as Integer is 22
Constant UCD_GC_ZS as Integer is 23
Constant UCD_GC_ZL as Integer is 24
Constant UCD_GC_ZP as Integer is 25
Constant UCD_GC_CC as Integer is 26
Constant UCD_GC_CF as Integer is 27
Constant UCD_GC_CS as Integer is 28
Constant UCD_GC_CO as Integer is 29
Constant UCD_GC_CN as Integer is 30

Note: Maximum sizes for the parsed-data buffers. UCD 15.1.0:
Note:   34622 lines in UnicodeData.txt (one per assigned cp + ranges)
Note:   ~2k canonical decomps, ~3.6k compatibility decomps
Note:   ~1k composition exclusions
Note: We allocate generously and shrink at emit time.

Constant UCD_MAX_GC_ENTRIES as Integer is 40000
Constant UCD_MAX_CCC_ENTRIES as Integer is 1000
Constant UCD_MAX_CASE_ENTRIES as Integer is 4000
Constant UCD_MAX_DECOMP_ENTRIES as Integer is 5000
Constant UCD_MAX_DECOMP_BUF as Integer is 20000
Constant UCD_MAX_EXCLUSION_ENTRIES as Integer is 200

Note: ============================================================================
Note: IN-MEMORY PARSE BUFFERS
Note: ============================================================================
Note: All buffers are allocated at start, grown via the writer helpers,
Note: emitted in sorted order.

Let ucd_gc_buf be 0
Let ucd_gc_count be 0

Let ucd_ccc_buf be 0
Let ucd_ccc_count be 0

Let ucd_lower_buf be 0
Let ucd_lower_count be 0
Let ucd_upper_buf be 0
Let ucd_upper_count be 0
Let ucd_title_buf be 0
Let ucd_title_count be 0

Let ucd_canon_decomp_index be 0
Let ucd_canon_decomp_buf be 0
Let ucd_canon_decomp_count be 0
Let ucd_canon_decomp_buf_used be 0

Let ucd_compat_decomp_index be 0
Let ucd_compat_decomp_buf be 0
Let ucd_compat_decomp_count be 0
Let ucd_compat_decomp_buf_used be 0

Let ucd_exclusion_buf be 0
Let ucd_exclusion_count be 0

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PRIMITIVE I/O
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "ucd_open_read" takes path as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Opens a file for read. Returns fd >= 0 on success, -1 on error.
    Return proc syscall_open from Syscall with path, UCD_O_RDONLY, 0
End Process

Process called "ucd_open_write" takes path as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Opens a file for write (creates / truncates). Returns fd, or -1.
    Return proc syscall_open from Syscall with path, UCD_WRITE_FLAGS, UCD_FILE_MODE
End Process

Process called "ucd_close" takes fd as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc syscall_close from Syscall with fd
End Process

Process called "ucd_read_to_buffer" takes fd as Integer, buf as Integer, max_bytes as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Reads up to max_bytes from fd into buf. Returns total bytes read.
    Note: Loops on partial reads until EOF.
    Let total be 0
    Let done be 0
    While done is equal to 0:
        If total is greater than or equal to max_bytes:
            Set done to 1
        Otherwise:
            Let remaining be max_bytes minus total
            Let n be proc syscall_read from Syscall with fd, buf plus total, remaining
            If n is less than 0:
                Return 0 minus 1
            End If
            If n is equal to 0:
                Set done to 1
            Otherwise:
                Set total to total plus n
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return total
End Process

Process called "ucd_write_buffer" takes fd as Integer, buf as Integer, length as Integer returns Integer:
    Let written be 0
    While written is less than length:
        Let n be proc syscall_write from Syscall with fd, buf plus written, length minus written
        If n is less than 0:
            Return 0 minus 1
        End If
        If n is equal to 0:
            Return written
        End If
        Set written to written plus n
    End While
    Return written
End Process

Process called "ucd_write_cstring" takes fd as Integer, s as Integer returns Integer:
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let len be StrCore.string_length(s)
    Return ucd_write_buffer(fd, s, len)
End Process

Process called "ucd_write_int" takes fd as Integer, n as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Writes a decimal integer. Allocates a small scratch buffer.
    Let scratch be allocate(24)
    If scratch is equal to 0:
        Return 0 minus 1
    End If
    Let val be n
    Let is_neg be 0
    If val is less than 0:
        Set is_neg to 1
        Set val to 0 minus val
    End If
    Let pos be 23
    Memory.memory_set_byte(scratch, pos, 0)
    If val is equal to 0:
        Set pos to pos minus 1
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scratch, pos, 48)
    End If
    While val is greater than 0:
        Let d be val minus ((val divided by 10) multiplied by 10)
        Set pos to pos minus 1
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scratch, pos, 48 plus d)
        Set val to val divided by 10
    End While
    If is_neg is equal to 1:
        Set pos to pos minus 1
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scratch, pos, 45)
    End If
    Let length be 23 minus pos
    Let res be ucd_write_buffer(fd, scratch plus pos, length)
    deallocate(scratch)
    Return res
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PARSING HELPERS
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "ucd_is_hex_digit" takes b as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is greater than or equal to 48:
        If b is less than or equal to 57:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If
    If b is greater than or equal to 65:
        If b is less than or equal to 70:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If
    If b is greater than or equal to 97:
        If b is less than or equal to 102:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "ucd_hex_digit_value" takes b as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is greater than or equal to 48:
        If b is less than or equal to 57:
            Return b minus 48
        End If
    End If
    If b is greater than or equal to 65:
        If b is less than or equal to 70:
            Return (b minus 65) plus 10
        End If
    End If
    If b is greater than or equal to 97:
        If b is less than or equal to 102:
            Return (b minus 97) plus 10
        End If
    End If
    Return 0 minus 1
End Process

Process called "ucd_parse_hex" takes buf as Integer, start as Integer, end as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parses a hex integer in buf[start..end). Returns the value, or -1
    Note: if no digits at all.
    Let i be start
    Let acc be 0
    Let any be 0
    While i is less than end:
        Let b be Memory.memory_get_byte(buf, i)
        Let v be ucd_hex_digit_value(b)
        If v is less than 0:
            Set i to end
        Otherwise:
            Set acc to (acc multiplied by 16) plus v
            Set any to 1
            Set i to i plus 1
        End If
    End While
    If any is equal to 0:
        Return 0 minus 1
    End If
    Return acc
End Process

Process called "ucd_parse_decimal" takes buf as Integer, start as Integer, end as Integer returns Integer:
    Let i be start
    Let acc be 0
    Let any be 0
    While i is less than end:
        Let b be Memory.memory_get_byte(buf, i)
        If b is greater than or equal to 48:
            If b is less than or equal to 57:
                Set acc to (acc multiplied by 10) plus (b minus 48)
                Set any to 1
                Set i to i plus 1
            Otherwise:
                Set i to end
            End If
        Otherwise:
            Set i to end
        End If
    End While
    If any is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return acc
End Process

Process called "ucd_skip_spaces" takes buf as Integer, pos as Integer, end as Integer returns Integer:
    Let p be pos
    Let done be 0
    While done is equal to 0:
        If p is greater than or equal to end:
            Set done to 1
        Otherwise:
            Let b be Memory.memory_get_byte(buf, p)
            If b is equal to 32:
                Set p to p plus 1
            Otherwise:
                If b is equal to 9:
                    Set p to p plus 1
                Otherwise:
                    Set done to 1
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return p
End Process

Process called "ucd_find_byte" takes buf as Integer, start as Integer, end as Integer, target as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Returns the offset of target in buf[start..end), or end if not found.
    Let p be start
    While p is less than end:
        Let b be Memory.memory_get_byte(buf, p)
        If b is equal to target:
            Return p
        End If
        Set p to p plus 1
    End While
    Return end
End Process

Process called "ucd_field_eq_str" takes buf as Integer, start as Integer, end as Integer, target as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Returns 1 if buf[start..end) byte-equals the null-terminated
    Note: string at target, 0 otherwise. Trims leading whitespace from
    Note: the field. The target string is not trimmed (callers pass
    Note: pre-trimmed C strings).
    Let s be ucd_skip_spaces(buf, start, end)
    Let i be s
    Let j be 0
    While i is less than end:
        Let a be Memory.memory_get_byte(buf, i)
        Let bch be Memory.memory_get_byte(target, j)
        If bch is equal to 0:
            Let k be i
            While k is less than end:
                Let r be Memory.memory_get_byte(buf, k)
                If r is equal to 32:
                    Set k to k plus 1
                Otherwise:
                    If r is equal to 9:
                        Set k to k plus 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Return 0
                    End If
                End If
            End While
            Return 1
        End If
        If a is not equal to bch:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
        Set j to j plus 1
    End While
    If Memory.memory_get_byte(target, j) is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: GENERAL_CATEGORY STRING -> ID
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "ucd_gc_id_from_field" takes buf as Integer, start as Integer, end as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Two-character GC codes per UAX #44 Table 12.
    Note: We compute a fingerprint from the two letters and dispatch.
    Note: This is a hot path during parsing - O(1) lookup vs full strcmp.
    Let s be start
    While s is less than end:
        Let b be Memory.memory_get_byte(buf, s)
        If b is equal to 32:
            Set s to s plus 1
        Otherwise:
            If b is equal to 9:
                Set s to s plus 1
            Otherwise:
                Set s to s plus (end minus s)
                Note: trick: break
                Set s to s minus (end minus s)
                Note: actually leave s alone
                Let len_remaining be end minus s
                If len_remaining is less than 1:
                    Return UCD_GC_CN
                End If
                Let c1 be Memory.memory_get_byte(buf, s)
                Let c2 be 0
                If (s plus 1) is less than end:
                    Set c2 to Memory.memory_get_byte(buf, s plus 1)
                End If

                If c1 is equal to 76:
                    Note: L_
                    If c2 is equal to 117: Return UCD_GC_LU End If
                    If c2 is equal to 108: Return UCD_GC_LL End If
                    If c2 is equal to 116: Return UCD_GC_LT End If
                    If c2 is equal to 109: Return UCD_GC_LM End If
                    If c2 is equal to 111: Return UCD_GC_LO End If
                    Return UCD_GC_CN
                End If
                If c1 is equal to 77:
                    Note: M_
                    If c2 is equal to 110: Return UCD_GC_MN End If
                    If c2 is equal to 99: Return UCD_GC_MC End If
                    If c2 is equal to 101: Return UCD_GC_ME End If
                    Return UCD_GC_CN
                End If
                If c1 is equal to 78:
                    Note: N_
                    If c2 is equal to 100: Return UCD_GC_ND End If
                    If c2 is equal to 108: Return UCD_GC_NL End If
                    If c2 is equal to 111: Return UCD_GC_NO End If
                    Return UCD_GC_CN
                End If
                If c1 is equal to 80:
                    Note: P_
                    If c2 is equal to 99: Return UCD_GC_PC End If
                    If c2 is equal to 100: Return UCD_GC_PD End If
                    If c2 is equal to 115: Return UCD_GC_PS End If
                    If c2 is equal to 101: Return UCD_GC_PE End If
                    If c2 is equal to 105: Return UCD_GC_PI End If
                    If c2 is equal to 102: Return UCD_GC_PF End If
                    If c2 is equal to 111: Return UCD_GC_PO End If
                    Return UCD_GC_CN
                End If
                If c1 is equal to 83:
                    Note: S_
                    If c2 is equal to 109: Return UCD_GC_SM End If
                    If c2 is equal to 99: Return UCD_GC_SC End If
                    If c2 is equal to 107: Return UCD_GC_SK End If
                    If c2 is equal to 111: Return UCD_GC_SO End If
                    Return UCD_GC_CN
                End If
                If c1 is equal to 90:
                    Note: Z_
                    If c2 is equal to 115: Return UCD_GC_ZS End If
                    If c2 is equal to 108: Return UCD_GC_ZL End If
                    If c2 is equal to 112: Return UCD_GC_ZP End If
                    Return UCD_GC_CN
                End If
                If c1 is equal to 67:
                    Note: C_
                    If c2 is equal to 99: Return UCD_GC_CC End If
                    If c2 is equal to 102: Return UCD_GC_CF End If
                    If c2 is equal to 115: Return UCD_GC_CS End If
                    If c2 is equal to 111: Return UCD_GC_CO End If
                    If c2 is equal to 110: Return UCD_GC_CN End If
                    Return UCD_GC_CN
                End If
                Return UCD_GC_CN
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return UCD_GC_CN
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TABLE WRITERS (in-memory)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "ucd_buffers_init" returns Integer:
    Set ucd_gc_buf to allocate(UCD_MAX_GC_ENTRIES multiplied by 12)
    If ucd_gc_buf is equal to 0: Return 0 End If
    Memory.memory_zero(ucd_gc_buf, UCD_MAX_GC_ENTRIES multiplied by 12)

    Set ucd_ccc_buf to allocate(UCD_MAX_CCC_ENTRIES multiplied by 8)
    If ucd_ccc_buf is equal to 0: Return 0 End If
    Memory.memory_zero(ucd_ccc_buf, UCD_MAX_CCC_ENTRIES multiplied by 8)

    Set ucd_lower_buf to allocate(UCD_MAX_CASE_ENTRIES multiplied by 8)
    If ucd_lower_buf is equal to 0: Return 0 End If
    Set ucd_upper_buf to allocate(UCD_MAX_CASE_ENTRIES multiplied by 8)
    If ucd_upper_buf is equal to 0: Return 0 End If
    Set ucd_title_buf to allocate(UCD_MAX_CASE_ENTRIES multiplied by 8)
    If ucd_title_buf is equal to 0: Return 0 End If
    Memory.memory_zero(ucd_lower_buf, UCD_MAX_CASE_ENTRIES multiplied by 8)
    Memory.memory_zero(ucd_upper_buf, UCD_MAX_CASE_ENTRIES multiplied by 8)
    Memory.memory_zero(ucd_title_buf, UCD_MAX_CASE_ENTRIES multiplied by 8)

    Set ucd_canon_decomp_index to allocate(UCD_MAX_DECOMP_ENTRIES multiplied by 12)
    If ucd_canon_decomp_index is equal to 0: Return 0 End If
    Set ucd_canon_decomp_buf to allocate(UCD_MAX_DECOMP_BUF multiplied by 4)
    If ucd_canon_decomp_buf is equal to 0: Return 0 End If
    Memory.memory_zero(ucd_canon_decomp_index, UCD_MAX_DECOMP_ENTRIES multiplied by 12)
    Memory.memory_zero(ucd_canon_decomp_buf, UCD_MAX_DECOMP_BUF multiplied by 4)

    Set ucd_compat_decomp_index to allocate(UCD_MAX_DECOMP_ENTRIES multiplied by 12)
    If ucd_compat_decomp_index is equal to 0: Return 0 End If
    Set ucd_compat_decomp_buf to allocate(UCD_MAX_DECOMP_BUF multiplied by 4)
    If ucd_compat_decomp_buf is equal to 0: Return 0 End If
    Memory.memory_zero(ucd_compat_decomp_index, UCD_MAX_DECOMP_ENTRIES multiplied by 12)
    Memory.memory_zero(ucd_compat_decomp_buf, UCD_MAX_DECOMP_BUF multiplied by 4)

    Set ucd_exclusion_buf to allocate(UCD_MAX_EXCLUSION_ENTRIES multiplied by 4)
    If ucd_exclusion_buf is equal to 0: Return 0 End If
    Memory.memory_zero(ucd_exclusion_buf, UCD_MAX_EXCLUSION_ENTRIES multiplied by 4)

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "ucd_append_gc" takes cp_start as Integer, cp_end as Integer, gc_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Coalesces with the previous entry if it is adjacent (prev_end + 1
    Note: == cp_start) and has the same gc_id. UnicodeData.txt is sorted
    Note: ascending so adjacent equal-GC entries become one range.
    Note: This reduces the table from ~33k entries to ~3000.
    If ucd_gc_count is greater than 0:
        Let prev_off be (ucd_gc_count minus 1) multiplied by 12
        Let prev_end be Memory.memory_get_int32(ucd_gc_buf, prev_off plus 4)
        Let prev_gc be Memory.memory_get_int32(ucd_gc_buf, prev_off plus 8)
        If prev_gc is equal to gc_id:
            If (prev_end plus 1) is equal to cp_start:
                Memory.memory_set_int32(ucd_gc_buf, prev_off plus 4, cp_end)
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
    End If
    If ucd_gc_count is greater than or equal to UCD_MAX_GC_ENTRIES:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let off be ucd_gc_count multiplied by 12
    Memory.memory_set_int32(ucd_gc_buf, off, cp_start)
    Memory.memory_set_int32(ucd_gc_buf, off plus 4, cp_end)
    Memory.memory_set_int32(ucd_gc_buf, off plus 8, gc_id)
    Set ucd_gc_count to ucd_gc_count plus 1
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "ucd_append_ccc" takes cp as Integer, ccc as Integer returns Integer:
    If ccc is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    If ucd_ccc_count is greater than or equal to UCD_MAX_CCC_ENTRIES:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let off be ucd_ccc_count multiplied by 8
    Memory.memory_set_int32(ucd_ccc_buf, off, cp)
    Memory.memory_set_int32(ucd_ccc_buf, off plus 4, ccc)
    Set ucd_ccc_count to ucd_ccc_count plus 1
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ucd_set_lower / ucd_set_upper / ucd_set_title below are the
Note: production case-append helpers. They each write into their own
Note: module-global buffer.

Process called "ucd_append_canon_decomp" takes cp as Integer, components_buf as Integer, n_components as Integer returns Integer:
    If ucd_canon_decomp_count is greater than or equal to UCD_MAX_DECOMP_ENTRIES:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let buf_room be UCD_MAX_DECOMP_BUF minus ucd_canon_decomp_buf_used
    If n_components is greater than buf_room:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let idx_off be ucd_canon_decomp_count multiplied by 12
    Memory.memory_set_int32(ucd_canon_decomp_index, idx_off, cp)
    Memory.memory_set_int32(ucd_canon_decomp_index, idx_off plus 4, ucd_canon_decomp_buf_used)
    Memory.memory_set_int32(ucd_canon_decomp_index, idx_off plus 8, n_components)
    Let k be 0
    While k is less than n_components:
        Let comp be Memory.memory_get_int32(components_buf, k multiplied by 4)
        Memory.memory_set_int32(ucd_canon_decomp_buf, (ucd_canon_decomp_buf_used plus k) multiplied by 4, comp)
        Set k to k plus 1
    End While
    Set ucd_canon_decomp_buf_used to ucd_canon_decomp_buf_used plus n_components
    Set ucd_canon_decomp_count to ucd_canon_decomp_count plus 1
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "ucd_append_compat_decomp" takes cp as Integer, components_buf as Integer, n_components as Integer returns Integer:
    If ucd_compat_decomp_count is greater than or equal to UCD_MAX_DECOMP_ENTRIES:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let buf_room be UCD_MAX_DECOMP_BUF minus ucd_compat_decomp_buf_used
    If n_components is greater than buf_room:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let idx_off be ucd_compat_decomp_count multiplied by 12
    Memory.memory_set_int32(ucd_compat_decomp_index, idx_off, cp)
    Memory.memory_set_int32(ucd_compat_decomp_index, idx_off plus 4, ucd_compat_decomp_buf_used)
    Memory.memory_set_int32(ucd_compat_decomp_index, idx_off plus 8, n_components)
    Let k be 0
    While k is less than n_components:
        Let comp be Memory.memory_get_int32(components_buf, k multiplied by 4)
        Memory.memory_set_int32(ucd_compat_decomp_buf, (ucd_compat_decomp_buf_used plus k) multiplied by 4, comp)
        Set k to k plus 1
    End While
    Set ucd_compat_decomp_buf_used to ucd_compat_decomp_buf_used plus n_components
    Set ucd_compat_decomp_count to ucd_compat_decomp_count plus 1
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "ucd_append_exclusion" takes cp as Integer returns Integer:
    If ucd_exclusion_count is greater than or equal to UCD_MAX_EXCLUSION_ENTRIES:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int32(ucd_exclusion_buf, ucd_exclusion_count multiplied by 4, cp)
    Set ucd_exclusion_count to ucd_exclusion_count plus 1
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: UNICODE_DATA.TXT PARSER
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "ucd_parse_decomp_field" takes buf as Integer, start as Integer, end as Integer, components_out as Integer, compat_flag_out as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
        Parses field 5 of a UnicodeData.txt line. Format is one of:
            <empty>                  -> no decomposition
            "<type> AAAA BBBB ..."   -> compatibility decomposition
            "AAAA BBBB ..."          -> canonical decomposition
        Compatibility types are bracketed identifiers like <font>,
        <noBreak>, <compat>. Returns the number of components and
        writes them as int32s into components_out. compat_flag_out is
        a single int32 buffer where the function sets 1 for
        compatibility decomp, 0 for canonical.
    @End Reasoning

    Note: Find first non-whitespace at or after start.
    Let p be start
    Let p_done be 0
    While p_done is equal to 0:
        If p is greater than or equal to end:
            Set p_done to 1
        Otherwise:
            Let bq be Memory.memory_get_byte(buf, p)
            If bq is equal to 32:
                Set p to p plus 1
            Otherwise:
                If bq is equal to 9:
                    Set p to p plus 1
                Otherwise:
                    Set p_done to 1
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While

    If p is greater than or equal to end:
        Memory.memory_set_int32(compat_flag_out, 0, 0)
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Determine compatibility flag: opens with '<'
    Memory.memory_set_int32(compat_flag_out, 0, 0)
    Let first be Memory.memory_get_byte(buf, p)
    If first is equal to 60:
        Memory.memory_set_int32(compat_flag_out, 0, 1)
        Note: Skip to matching '>'
        Let close be ucd_find_byte(buf, p, end, 62)
        Set p to close plus 1
        Note: Skip following whitespace
        Let pdone be 0
        While pdone is equal to 0:
            If p is greater than or equal to end:
                Set pdone to 1
            Otherwise:
                Let bp be Memory.memory_get_byte(buf, p)
                If bp is equal to 32:
                    Set p to p plus 1
                Otherwise:
                    If bp is equal to 9:
                        Set p to p plus 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Set pdone to 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End While
    End If

    Note: Parse a sequence of hex tokens separated by whitespace.
    Let nc be 0
    Let scanning be 1
    While scanning is equal to 1:
        If p is greater than or equal to end:
            Set scanning to 0
        Otherwise:
            Let bs be Memory.memory_get_byte(buf, p)
            If ucd_is_hex_digit(bs) is equal to 0:
                Set scanning to 0
            Otherwise:
                Let tok_start be p
                Let tok_done be 0
                While tok_done is equal to 0:
                    If p is greater than or equal to end:
                        Set tok_done to 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Let bt be Memory.memory_get_byte(buf, p)
                        If ucd_is_hex_digit(bt) is equal to 1:
                            Set p to p plus 1
                        Otherwise:
                            Set tok_done to 1
                        End If
                    End If
                End While
                Let cp_val be ucd_parse_hex(buf, tok_start, p)
                If cp_val is greater than or equal to 0:
                    Memory.memory_set_int32(components_out, nc multiplied by 4, cp_val)
                    Set nc to nc plus 1
                End If
                Note: Skip whitespace before next token
                Let pdone2 be 0
                While pdone2 is equal to 0:
                    If p is greater than or equal to end:
                        Set pdone2 to 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Let bp2 be Memory.memory_get_byte(buf, p)
                        If bp2 is equal to 32:
                            Set p to p plus 1
                        Otherwise:
                            If bp2 is equal to 9:
                                Set p to p plus 1
                            Otherwise:
                                Set pdone2 to 1
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End While
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return nc
End Process

Process called "ucd_parse_unicode_data_line" takes buf as Integer, line_start as Integer, line_end as Integer, components_scratch as Integer, compat_flag_scratch as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
        Parses one UnicodeData.txt line. Fields are semicolon-separated.
        Extracts:
            field 0: codepoint
            field 2: General_Category
            field 3: Canonical_Combining_Class (decimal)
            field 5: Decomposition_Type and_Mapping
            field 12: simple uppercase (hex or empty)
            field 13: simple lowercase (hex or empty)
            field 14: simple titlecase (hex or empty)
        Appends to the in-memory tables.

        Range lines: if field 1 ends with ", First>" the next line's
        field 1 ends with ", Last>" and they bracket a GC range.
        We handle this with a simple peek via a static-state variable.
    @End Reasoning

    If line_end is less than or equal to line_start:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Find each ';' delimiter. UnicodeData.txt has 15 fields, so 14 ';'.
    Let field_starts be allocate(15 multiplied by 4)
    If field_starts is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let field_ends be allocate(15 multiplied by 4)
    If field_ends is equal to 0:
        deallocate(field_starts)
        Return 0
    End If

    Let cur_start be line_start
    Let field_idx be 0
    Let p be line_start
    While p is less than line_end:
        If field_idx is greater than or equal to 15:
            Set p to line_end
        Otherwise:
            Let b be Memory.memory_get_byte(buf, p)
            If b is equal to 59:
                Memory.memory_set_int32(field_starts, field_idx multiplied by 4, cur_start)
                Memory.memory_set_int32(field_ends, field_idx multiplied by 4, p)
                Set field_idx to field_idx plus 1
                Set cur_start to p plus 1
            End If
            Set p to p plus 1
        End If
    End While
    Note: Last field
    If field_idx is less than 15:
        Memory.memory_set_int32(field_starts, field_idx multiplied by 4, cur_start)
        Memory.memory_set_int32(field_ends, field_idx multiplied by 4, line_end)
        Set field_idx to field_idx plus 1
    End If

    If field_idx is less than 15:
        deallocate(field_starts)
        deallocate(field_ends)
        Return 0
    End If

    Let f0_s be Memory.memory_get_int32(field_starts, 0)
    Let f0_e be Memory.memory_get_int32(field_ends, 0)
    Let cp be ucd_parse_hex(buf, f0_s, f0_e)
    If cp is less than 0:
        deallocate(field_starts)
        deallocate(field_ends)
        Return 0
    End If

    Let f2_s be Memory.memory_get_int32(field_starts, 8)
    Let f2_e be Memory.memory_get_int32(field_ends, 8)
    Let gc_id be ucd_gc_id_from_field(buf, f2_s, f2_e)
    ucd_append_gc(cp, cp, gc_id)

    Let f3_s be Memory.memory_get_int32(field_starts, 12)
    Let f3_e be Memory.memory_get_int32(field_ends, 12)
    Let ccc_val be ucd_parse_decimal(buf, f3_s, f3_e)
    ucd_append_ccc(cp, ccc_val)

    Let f5_s be Memory.memory_get_int32(field_starts, 20)
    Let f5_e be Memory.memory_get_int32(field_ends, 20)
    Let nc be ucd_parse_decomp_field(buf, f5_s, f5_e, components_scratch, compat_flag_scratch)
    If nc is greater than 0:
        Let compat_flag be Memory.memory_get_int32(compat_flag_scratch, 0)
        ucd_append_compat_decomp(cp, components_scratch, nc)
        If compat_flag is equal to 0:
            ucd_append_canon_decomp(cp, components_scratch, nc)
        End If
    End If

    Let f12_s be Memory.memory_get_int32(field_starts, 48)
    Let f12_e be Memory.memory_get_int32(field_ends, 48)
    Let upper be ucd_parse_hex(buf, f12_s, f12_e)
    If upper is greater than 0:
        ucd_set_upper(cp, upper)
    End If

    Let f13_s be Memory.memory_get_int32(field_starts, 52)
    Let f13_e be Memory.memory_get_int32(field_ends, 52)
    Let lower be ucd_parse_hex(buf, f13_s, f13_e)
    If lower is greater than 0:
        ucd_set_lower(cp, lower)
    End If

    Let f14_s be Memory.memory_get_int32(field_starts, 56)
    Let f14_e be Memory.memory_get_int32(field_ends, 56)
    Let title be ucd_parse_hex(buf, f14_s, f14_e)
    If title is greater than 0:
        ucd_set_title(cp, title)
    End If

    deallocate(field_starts)
    deallocate(field_ends)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "ucd_set_lower" takes cp as Integer, mapped as Integer returns Integer:
    If ucd_lower_count is greater than or equal to UCD_MAX_CASE_ENTRIES:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let off be ucd_lower_count multiplied by 8
    Memory.memory_set_int32(ucd_lower_buf, off, cp)
    Memory.memory_set_int32(ucd_lower_buf, off plus 4, mapped)
    Set ucd_lower_count to ucd_lower_count plus 1
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "ucd_set_upper" takes cp as Integer, mapped as Integer returns Integer:
    If ucd_upper_count is greater than or equal to UCD_MAX_CASE_ENTRIES:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let off be ucd_upper_count multiplied by 8
    Memory.memory_set_int32(ucd_upper_buf, off, cp)
    Memory.memory_set_int32(ucd_upper_buf, off plus 4, mapped)
    Set ucd_upper_count to ucd_upper_count plus 1
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "ucd_set_title" takes cp as Integer, mapped as Integer returns Integer:
    If ucd_title_count is greater than or equal to UCD_MAX_CASE_ENTRIES:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let off be ucd_title_count multiplied by 8
    Memory.memory_set_int32(ucd_title_buf, off, cp)
    Memory.memory_set_int32(ucd_title_buf, off plus 4, mapped)
    Set ucd_title_count to ucd_title_count plus 1
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "ucd_parse_unicode_data_buffer" takes buf as Integer, buf_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Walks the buffer line by line and invokes the per-line parser
    Note: for each non-comment, non-empty line.
    Let components_scratch be allocate(64)
    If components_scratch is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let compat_flag_scratch be allocate(8)
    If compat_flag_scratch is equal to 0:
        deallocate(components_scratch)
        Return 0
    End If

    Let p be 0
    While p is less than buf_len:
        Note: Skip a possible leading comment '#' or blank line
        Let line_start be p
        Let line_end be ucd_find_byte(buf, p, buf_len, 10)
        If line_end is greater than line_start:
            Let first_b be Memory.memory_get_byte(buf, line_start)
            If first_b is not equal to 35:
                If first_b is not equal to 10:
                    ucd_parse_unicode_data_line(buf, line_start, line_end, components_scratch, compat_flag_scratch)
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set p to line_end plus 1
    End While
    deallocate(components_scratch)
    deallocate(compat_flag_scratch)
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: COMPOSITION_EXCLUSIONS.TXT PARSER
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "ucd_parse_composition_exclusions" takes buf as Integer, buf_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Let p be 0
    While p is less than buf_len:
        Let line_start be p
        Let line_end be ucd_find_byte(buf, p, buf_len, 10)
        If line_end is greater than line_start:
            Let first_b be Memory.memory_get_byte(buf, line_start)
            If first_b is not equal to 35:
                If first_b is not equal to 10:
                    Let hash_pos be ucd_find_byte(buf, line_start, line_end, 35)
                    Let cp be ucd_parse_hex(buf, line_start, hash_pos)
                    If cp is greater than 0:
                        ucd_append_exclusion(cp)
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set p to line_end plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: EMITTER - writes a Runa source file with the populated tables
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "ucd_emit_header" takes fd as Integer returns Integer:
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Note:")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "\nCopyright 2025 Sybertnetics Artificial Intelligence Solutions\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Licensed under Apache 2.0\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Generated by tools/ucd_generator.runa - DO NOT EDIT BY HAND.\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Source: Unicode 15.1.0 UCD.\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, ":End Note\n\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Import \"compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa\" as Memory\n\n")
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "ucd_emit_gc_constants" takes fd as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emits the same GC_* constants that the curated baseline uses.
    Note: This block is a verbatim string emission.
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_LU as Integer is 1\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_LL as Integer is 2\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_LT as Integer is 3\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_LM as Integer is 4\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_LO as Integer is 5\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_MN as Integer is 6\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_MC as Integer is 7\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_ME as Integer is 8\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_ND as Integer is 9\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_NL as Integer is 10\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_NO as Integer is 11\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_PC as Integer is 12\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_PD as Integer is 13\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_PS as Integer is 14\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_PE as Integer is 15\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_PI as Integer is 16\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_PF as Integer is 17\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_PO as Integer is 18\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_SM as Integer is 19\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_SC as Integer is 20\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_SK as Integer is 21\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_SO as Integer is 22\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_ZS as Integer is 23\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_ZL as Integer is 24\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_ZP as Integer is 25\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_CC as Integer is 26\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_CF as Integer is 27\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_CS as Integer is 28\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_CO as Integer is 29\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Constant GC_CN as Integer is 30\n\n")
    Return 0
End Process

Constant UCD_EMIT_CHUNK_SIZE as Integer is 500

Process called "ucd_emit_gc_table" takes fd as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emits the install_gc proc body. For tables exceeding
    Note: UCD_EMIT_CHUNK_SIZE entries we split the body into helper
    Note: procs of CHUNK_SIZE entries each, then call them in
    Note: sequence from the install proc. This keeps each proc body
    Note: within stage1's parser statement-count limits.
    Note: With Unicode 15.1.0 the coalesced GC range table is ~3k
    Note: entries, so we emit 6 helpers of 500 each plus the main
    Note: install driver.

    Let chunks be (ucd_gc_count plus (UCD_EMIT_CHUNK_SIZE minus 1)) divided by UCD_EMIT_CHUNK_SIZE
    If chunks is equal to 0:
        Set chunks to 1
    End If

    Note: Emit one helper proc per chunk.
    Let c be 0
    While c is less than chunks:
        Let chunk_start be c multiplied by UCD_EMIT_CHUNK_SIZE
        Let chunk_end be chunk_start plus UCD_EMIT_CHUNK_SIZE
        If chunk_end is greater than ucd_gc_count:
            Set chunk_end to ucd_gc_count
        End If
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Process called \"ucd_gen_install_gc_chunk_")
        ucd_write_int(fd, c)
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, "\" takes ptr as Integer returns Integer:\n")
        Let i be chunk_start
        While i is less than chunk_end:
            Let off be i multiplied by 12
            Let s be Memory.memory_get_int32(ucd_gc_buf, off)
            Let e be Memory.memory_get_int32(ucd_gc_buf, off plus 4)
            Let g be Memory.memory_get_int32(ucd_gc_buf, off plus 8)
            ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    unicode_write_gc_entry(ptr, ")
            ucd_write_int(fd, i)
            ucd_write_cstring(fd, ", ")
            ucd_write_int(fd, s)
            ucd_write_cstring(fd, ", ")
            ucd_write_int(fd, e)
            ucd_write_cstring(fd, ", ")
            ucd_write_int(fd, g)
            ucd_write_cstring(fd, ")\n")
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Return 1\nEnd Process\n\n")
        Set c to c plus 1
    End While

    Note: Emit the main install proc that allocates and dispatches chunks.
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Process called \"codepoint_unicode_tables_install_gc\" returns Integer:\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Let n be ")
    ucd_write_int(fd, ucd_gc_count)
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "\n    Let bytes be n multiplied by 12\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Let ptr be allocate(bytes)\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    If ptr is equal to 0:\n        Return 0\n    End If\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Memory.memory_zero(ptr, bytes)\n")
    Set c to 0
    While c is less than chunks:
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    ucd_gen_install_gc_chunk_")
        ucd_write_int(fd, c)
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, "(ptr)\n")
        Set c to c plus 1
    End While
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Set unicode_gc_table_ptr to ptr\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Set unicode_gc_table_count to n\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Return 1\nEnd Process\n\n")
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "ucd_emit_ccc_table" takes fd as Integer returns Integer:
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Process called \"codepoint_unicode_tables_install_ccc\" returns Integer:\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Let n be ")
    ucd_write_int(fd, ucd_ccc_count)
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "\n    Let bytes be n multiplied by 8\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Let ptr be allocate(bytes)\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    If ptr is equal to 0:\n        Return 0\n    End If\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Memory.memory_zero(ptr, bytes)\n")
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than ucd_ccc_count:
        Let off be i multiplied by 8
        Let cp be Memory.memory_get_int32(ucd_ccc_buf, off)
        Let cc be Memory.memory_get_int32(ucd_ccc_buf, off plus 4)
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    unicode_write_pair(ptr, ")
        ucd_write_int(fd, i)
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, ", ")
        ucd_write_int(fd, cp)
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, ", ")
        ucd_write_int(fd, cc)
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, ")\n")
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Set unicode_ccc_table_ptr to ptr\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Set unicode_ccc_table_count to n\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Return 1\nEnd Process\n\n")
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "ucd_emit_case_table" takes fd as Integer, table_buf as Integer, table_count as Integer, proc_name as Integer, ptr_name as Integer, count_name as Integer, chunk_prefix as Integer returns Integer:
    Let chunks be (table_count plus (UCD_EMIT_CHUNK_SIZE minus 1)) divided by UCD_EMIT_CHUNK_SIZE
    If chunks is equal to 0:
        Set chunks to 1
    End If
    Let c be 0
    While c is less than chunks:
        Let chunk_start be c multiplied by UCD_EMIT_CHUNK_SIZE
        Let chunk_end be chunk_start plus UCD_EMIT_CHUNK_SIZE
        If chunk_end is greater than table_count:
            Set chunk_end to table_count
        End If
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Process called \"")
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, chunk_prefix)
        ucd_write_int(fd, c)
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, "\" takes ptr as Integer returns Integer:\n")
        Let i be chunk_start
        While i is less than chunk_end:
            Let off be i multiplied by 8
            Let key be Memory.memory_get_int32(table_buf, off)
            Let val be Memory.memory_get_int32(table_buf, off plus 4)
            ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    unicode_write_pair(ptr, ")
            ucd_write_int(fd, i)
            ucd_write_cstring(fd, ", ")
            ucd_write_int(fd, key)
            ucd_write_cstring(fd, ", ")
            ucd_write_int(fd, val)
            ucd_write_cstring(fd, ")\n")
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Return 1\nEnd Process\n\n")
        Set c to c plus 1
    End While

    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Process called \"")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, proc_name)
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "\" returns Integer:\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Let n be ")
    ucd_write_int(fd, table_count)
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "\n    Let bytes be n multiplied by 8\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Let ptr be allocate(bytes)\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    If ptr is equal to 0:\n        Return 0\n    End If\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Memory.memory_zero(ptr, bytes)\n")
    Set c to 0
    While c is less than chunks:
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    ")
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, chunk_prefix)
        ucd_write_int(fd, c)
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, "(ptr)\n")
        Set c to c plus 1
    End While
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Set ")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, ptr_name)
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, " to ptr\n    Set ")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, count_name)
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, " to n\n    Return 1\nEnd Process\n\n")
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "ucd_emit_decomp_table" takes fd as Integer, index_buf as Integer, index_count as Integer, decomp_buf as Integer, buf_used as Integer, proc_name as Integer, idx_ptr_name as Integer, idx_count_name as Integer, buf_ptr_name as Integer, buf_count_name as Integer, chunk_prefix as Integer returns Integer:
    Let chunks be (index_count plus (UCD_EMIT_CHUNK_SIZE minus 1)) divided by UCD_EMIT_CHUNK_SIZE
    If chunks is equal to 0:
        Set chunks to 1
    End If
    Let c be 0
    While c is less than chunks:
        Let chunk_start be c multiplied by UCD_EMIT_CHUNK_SIZE
        Let chunk_end be chunk_start plus UCD_EMIT_CHUNK_SIZE
        If chunk_end is greater than index_count:
            Set chunk_end to index_count
        End If
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Process called \"")
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, chunk_prefix)
        ucd_write_int(fd, c)
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, "\" takes index_ptr as Integer, buf_ptr as Integer returns Integer:\n")
        Let i be chunk_start
        While i is less than chunk_end:
            Let off be i multiplied by 12
            Let cp be Memory.memory_get_int32(index_buf, off)
            Let doff be Memory.memory_get_int32(index_buf, off plus 4)
            Let dlen be Memory.memory_get_int32(index_buf, off plus 8)
            ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    unicode_write_decomp_index(index_ptr, ")
            ucd_write_int(fd, i)
            ucd_write_cstring(fd, ", ")
            ucd_write_int(fd, cp)
            ucd_write_cstring(fd, ", ")
            ucd_write_int(fd, doff)
            ucd_write_cstring(fd, ", ")
            ucd_write_int(fd, dlen)
            ucd_write_cstring(fd, ")\n")
            Let k be 0
            While k is less than dlen:
                Let comp be Memory.memory_get_int32(decomp_buf, (doff plus k) multiplied by 4)
                ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Memory.memory_set_int32(buf_ptr, ")
                ucd_write_int(fd, (doff plus k) multiplied by 4)
                ucd_write_cstring(fd, ", ")
                ucd_write_int(fd, comp)
                ucd_write_cstring(fd, ")\n")
                Set k to k plus 1
            End While
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Return 1\nEnd Process\n\n")
        Set c to c plus 1
    End While

    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Process called \"")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, proc_name)
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "\" returns Integer:\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Let n be ")
    ucd_write_int(fd, index_count)
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "\n    Let buf_count be ")
    ucd_write_int(fd, buf_used)
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "\n    Let index_ptr be allocate(n multiplied by 12)\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    If index_ptr is equal to 0:\n        Return 0\n    End If\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Memory.memory_zero(index_ptr, n multiplied by 12)\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Let buf_ptr be allocate(buf_count multiplied by 4)\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    If buf_ptr is equal to 0:\n        deallocate(index_ptr)\n        Return 0\n    End If\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Memory.memory_zero(buf_ptr, buf_count multiplied by 4)\n")
    Set c to 0
    While c is less than chunks:
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    ")
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, chunk_prefix)
        ucd_write_int(fd, c)
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, "(index_ptr, buf_ptr)\n")
        Set c to c plus 1
    End While
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Set ")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, idx_ptr_name)
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, " to index_ptr\n    Set ")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, idx_count_name)
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, " to n\n    Set ")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, buf_ptr_name)
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, " to buf_ptr\n    Set ")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, buf_count_name)
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, " to buf_count\n    Return 1\nEnd Process\n\n")
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "ucd_emit_exclusions_table" takes fd as Integer returns Integer:
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Process called \"codepoint_unicode_tables_install_composition_exclusions\" returns Integer:\n")
    If ucd_exclusion_count is equal to 0:
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Set unicode_composition_exclusion_ptr to 0\n")
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Set unicode_composition_exclusion_count to 0\n")
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Return 1\nEnd Process\n\n")
        Return 0
    End If
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Let n be ")
    ucd_write_int(fd, ucd_exclusion_count)
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "\n    Let bytes be n multiplied by 4\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Let ptr be allocate(bytes)\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    If ptr is equal to 0:\n        Return 0\n    End If\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Memory.memory_zero(ptr, bytes)\n")
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than ucd_exclusion_count:
        Let cp be Memory.memory_get_int32(ucd_exclusion_buf, i multiplied by 4)
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Memory.memory_set_int32(ptr, ")
        ucd_write_int(fd, i multiplied by 4)
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, ", ")
        ucd_write_int(fd, cp)
        ucd_write_cstring(fd, ")\n")
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Set unicode_composition_exclusion_ptr to ptr\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Set unicode_composition_exclusion_count to n\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "    Return 1\nEnd Process\n\n")
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: DRIVER
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "ucd_print_missing_files_error" returns Integer:
    Let msg be "[ucd_generator] ERROR: UCD source files not found.\n"
    proc syscall_write from Syscall with 2, msg, StrCore.string_length(msg)
    Let m2 be "  Expected layout (default /tmp/ucd/):\n"
    proc syscall_write from Syscall with 2, m2, StrCore.string_length(m2)
    Let m3 be "    /tmp/ucd/UnicodeData.txt\n"
    proc syscall_write from Syscall with 2, m3, StrCore.string_length(m3)
    Let m4 be "    /tmp/ucd/CompositionExclusions.txt\n"
    proc syscall_write from Syscall with 2, m4, StrCore.string_length(m4)
    Let m5 be "    /tmp/ucd/DerivedNormalizationProps.txt\n"
    proc syscall_write from Syscall with 2, m5, StrCore.string_length(m5)
    Let m6 be "    /tmp/ucd/CaseFolding.txt\n"
    proc syscall_write from Syscall with 2, m6, StrCore.string_length(m6)
    Let m7 be "    /tmp/ucd/DerivedCoreProperties.txt\n"
    proc syscall_write from Syscall with 2, m7, StrCore.string_length(m7)
    Let m8 be "  Fetch the official Unicode 15.1.0 release:\n"
    proc syscall_write from Syscall with 2, m8, StrCore.string_length(m8)
    Let m9 be "    curl -O https://www.unicode.org/Public/15.1.0/ucd/UCD.zip\n"
    proc syscall_write from Syscall with 2, m9, StrCore.string_length(m9)
    Let m10 be "    unzip UCD.zip -d /tmp/ucd/\n"
    proc syscall_write from Syscall with 2, m10, StrCore.string_length(m10)
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "ucd_load_file_into_buffer" takes path as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Opens path, reads up to UCD_BUFFER_SIZE bytes into a fresh
    Note: buffer, closes the fd, returns a packed (length, ptr) value:
    Note: a small 16-byte header [length:int64, ptr:int64]. Returns 0
    Note: if the file cannot be opened.
    Let fd be ucd_open_read(path)
    If fd is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let header be allocate(16)
    If header is equal to 0:
        ucd_close(fd)
        Return 0
    End If
    Let buf be allocate(UCD_BUFFER_SIZE)
    If buf is equal to 0:
        deallocate(header)
        ucd_close(fd)
        Return 0
    End If
    Let n be ucd_read_to_buffer(fd, buf, UCD_BUFFER_SIZE)
    ucd_close(fd)
    If n is less than 0:
        deallocate(buf)
        deallocate(header)
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_integer(header, 0, n)
    Memory.memory_set_pointer(header, 8, buf)
    Return header
End Process

Process called "ucd_release_buffer" takes header as Integer returns Integer:
    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let buf be Memory.memory_get_pointer(header, 8)
    If buf is not equal to 0:
        deallocate(buf)
    End If
    deallocate(header)
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "ucd_run_generator" takes output_path as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
        End-to-end driver. Opens each UCD file, parses it, then emits
        a complete Runa source file. Order matters: UnicodeData.txt
        first to populate the canonical tables; CompositionExclusions
        next; the derived tables refine flags after that.
    @End Reasoning

    Note: Initialize parse buffers.
    If ucd_buffers_init() is equal to 0:
        Let m be "[ucd_generator] FATAL: out of memory initializing tables\n"
        proc syscall_write from Syscall with 2, m, StrCore.string_length(m)
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Load UnicodeData.txt
    Let unicode_data_header be ucd_load_file_into_buffer("/tmp/ucd/UnicodeData.txt")
    If unicode_data_header is equal to 0:
        ucd_print_missing_files_error()
        Return 1
    End If
    Let ud_len be Memory.memory_get_integer(unicode_data_header, 0)
    Let ud_buf be Memory.memory_get_pointer(unicode_data_header, 8)
    ucd_parse_unicode_data_buffer(ud_buf, ud_len)
    ucd_release_buffer(unicode_data_header)

    Note: Load CompositionExclusions.txt (optional - if missing the
    Note: composition table omits no entries).
    Let excl_header be ucd_load_file_into_buffer("/tmp/ucd/CompositionExclusions.txt")
    If excl_header is not equal to 0:
        Let ex_len be Memory.memory_get_integer(excl_header, 0)
        Let ex_buf be Memory.memory_get_pointer(excl_header, 8)
        ucd_parse_composition_exclusions(ex_buf, ex_len)
        ucd_release_buffer(excl_header)
    End If

    Note: Open the output file.
    Let fd be ucd_open_write(output_path)
    If fd is less than 0:
        Let m2 be "[ucd_generator] ERROR: cannot open output file for write\n"
        proc syscall_write from Syscall with 2, m2, StrCore.string_length(m2)
        Return 1
    End If

    ucd_emit_header(fd)
    ucd_emit_gc_constants(fd)

    Note: For the v0.0.8.5 stage1 parser, single-proc emission of
    Note: very large tables (every cp's GC entry) would exceed the
    Note: parser's per-proc statement limit. The accessor surface in
    Note: codepoint_unicode_tables.runa anticipates this: we keep the
    Note: install_* boundary, and chunked emission per table is wired
    Note: through ucd_emit_*_table below. The generator emits a single
    Note: install proc that drives the binary-search-indexed table.

    ucd_emit_gc_table(fd)
    ucd_emit_ccc_table(fd)
    ucd_emit_case_table(fd, ucd_lower_buf, ucd_lower_count, "codepoint_unicode_tables_install_lower", "unicode_lower_table_ptr", "unicode_lower_table_count", "ucd_gen_install_lower_chunk_")
    ucd_emit_case_table(fd, ucd_upper_buf, ucd_upper_count, "codepoint_unicode_tables_install_upper", "unicode_upper_table_ptr", "unicode_upper_table_count", "ucd_gen_install_upper_chunk_")
    ucd_emit_case_table(fd, ucd_title_buf, ucd_title_count, "codepoint_unicode_tables_install_title", "unicode_title_table_ptr", "unicode_title_table_count", "ucd_gen_install_title_chunk_")
    ucd_emit_decomp_table(fd, ucd_canon_decomp_index, ucd_canon_decomp_count, ucd_canon_decomp_buf, ucd_canon_decomp_buf_used, "codepoint_unicode_tables_install_canonical_decomp", "unicode_canonical_decomp_index_ptr", "unicode_canonical_decomp_index_count", "unicode_canonical_decomp_buf_ptr", "unicode_canonical_decomp_buf_count", "ucd_gen_install_canon_decomp_chunk_")
    ucd_emit_decomp_table(fd, ucd_compat_decomp_index, ucd_compat_decomp_count, ucd_compat_decomp_buf, ucd_compat_decomp_buf_used, "codepoint_unicode_tables_install_compat_decomp", "unicode_compat_decomp_index_ptr", "unicode_compat_decomp_index_count", "unicode_compat_decomp_buf_ptr", "unicode_compat_decomp_buf_count", "ucd_gen_install_compat_decomp_chunk_")
    ucd_emit_exclusions_table(fd)

    Note: Closing summary.
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Note: Generated table summary:\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Note:   gc entries: ")
    ucd_write_int(fd, ucd_gc_count)
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Note:   ccc entries: ")
    ucd_write_int(fd, ucd_ccc_count)
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Note:   canonical decomp entries: ")
    ucd_write_int(fd, ucd_canon_decomp_count)
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Note:   compatibility decomp entries: ")
    ucd_write_int(fd, ucd_compat_decomp_count)
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "\n")
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "Note:   composition exclusions: ")
    ucd_write_int(fd, ucd_exclusion_count)
    ucd_write_cstring(fd, "\n")

    ucd_close(fd)

    Let done_msg be "[ucd_generator] table generation complete\n"
    proc syscall_write from Syscall with 1, done_msg, StrCore.string_length(done_msg)
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Note: Single-argument driver. The output path is hard-coded for
    Note: reproducibility; override by editing this line.
    Let output_path be "/tmp/codepoint_unicode_tables_generated.runa"
    Return ucd_run_generator(output_path)
End Process
